    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>This retrospective study utilized healthcare claims data to investigate the incidence, patient demographics, and concurrent diagnoses associated with long COVID in the U.S. Medicare population. Nearly 194,000 (0.6%) beneficiaries had post-COVID condition diagnoses, with higher rates among nursing home residents. Of those medically attended for COVID-19, 3-5% were diagnosed with post-COVID conditions. We observed minimal demographic differences between those with and without long COVID. When comparing diagnoses concurrent with long COVID and COVID-19, certain codes (G72 and J84) for myopathies and interstitial pulmonary diseases were disproportionately present with long COVID.</jats:p>",
